//////////////////////////

Recommendations

.To reduce risks and improve Botium Toys’ security posture, the IT Manager should prioritize the following:

.Implement Access Control Policies:

   .Enforce least privilege and separation of duties to restrict unnecessary data access.

   .Develop and deploy a centralized password management system.

.Data Protection Enhancements:

   .Enable encryption for all sensitive and financial data (at rest and in transit).

   .Implement tokenization or hashing for stored cardholder data.

.Compliance and Regulatory Alignment:

   .Achieve PCI DSS and GDPR compliance through controlled access, encryption, and secure transmission of customer data.

   .Develop clear user access policies aligned with SOC 2 requirements.

.Disaster Recovery and Business Continuity:

   .Create and regularly test backup and disaster recovery plans.

   .Store backups securely off-site or in the cloud.

.Security Monitoring:

   .Deploy an Intrusion Detection System (IDS) and consider an SIEM (Security Information and Event Management) solution for real-time monitoring.

   .Schedule routine vulnerability assessments and penetration tests.

.Password and Authentication Improvements:

   .Strengthen the password policy (e.g., 12+ characters, special symbols, MFA).

   .Roll out multi-factor authentication (MFA) across systems.

.Legacy System Management:

   .Create a maintenance schedule and formal retirement plan for end-of-life systems.

.Continuous Training and Awareness:

    .Conduct employee cybersecurity awareness training to reduce human error risks.

